<T extends CsvItemType>(
  csvString: string
): T[] | null => {
  const [columnsString, ...rowStrings] = csvString.split("\n");

  const columns = columnsString.split(",").map((x) => x.trim());

  const rows = rowStrings.map((rowString) => {
    const values = rowString.split(",");

    const rowObject = mergeObjectsArray(
      columns.map((columnName, index) => {
        return { [columnName]: parsePrimitive(values[index]) };
      })
    ) as T;

    return rowObject;
  });

  return rows;
}
name: tryParseCsv
description: This function parses a CSV into the object it says it has in the header
